\section{QW eigenvalues}
The eigenvalue equation for QW bound states is given by ${\eta^{(e)}}={\eta^{(h)}}=0$.
Figure \ref{fig:S1} summarizes positive eigenvalues ${E_n}$ ($n=1,2,3,\cdots$) for electron subbands at ${k_y}=0$ as a function of $a$.
Note that negative eigenvalues $-{E_n}$ are relevant to hole subbands in consequence of electron-hole symmetry.
The QAH conduction via chiral mode is observable in the QW gap $\left|E\right|<{E_1}$.
As $\left|m\right|\to\infty$, $r_{21}^{(e)}r_{23}^{(e)}$ approaches unity so that ${E_n}=\gamma\sqrt{{k_y}^2+{{(n\pi/2a)}^2}}$.
